// nodule: compiler.lex
// @version: 0.1.0
// @license: MIT
// @authors: Tyler Zervas
// @since: 2026-07-05
// @updated: 2026-07-05
// @summary: Self-hosted L1 lexer (M-740 Stage 1; DN-26 §7.3 row 1). A faithful port of
//   crates/mycelium-l1/src/lexer.rs's `lex` entry (the plain, comment-discarding path) over the
//   token/position types this nodule redeclares from `compiler.token` (see FLAG-lex-0).
nodule compiler.lex;

// M-740 (E18-1, DN-26 §7.3 Stage 1). `crates/mycelium-l1/src/lexer.rs` stays the trusted
// differential oracle (DN-26 §7.4); this file is checked against it by
// `crates/mycelium-l1/tests/compiler_stage1.rs` (token-stream differential over the accept-corpus).
//
// FLAG-lex-0 (self-contained; redeclares compiler.token). Per token.myc's own FLAG-token-4:
// cross-nodule EXECUTION is staged today (`checkty.rs`'s `check_phylum` doc comment, ~line 1118:
// "running a `use`d fn across nodules is a follow-up ... a cross-nodule call lowers to a
// never-silent Unsupported/Residual"). So this nodule cannot `use compiler.token.*` and actually
// RUN `keyword`/`Tok`/`Pos`/`Spanned` yet; it redeclares them byte-for-byte identically, mirroring
// the established stdlib self-containment convention (`lib/std/text.myc`). Once cross-nodule
// execution lands, a follow-up can delete this duplication and `use` the sibling nodule instead —
// not this leaf's call to make (FLAGged up).
//
// Representation choices/deviations (each deliberate + honest — VR-5/G2):
//
// FLAG-lex-1 (source as Bytes, not Vec<char>). Rust's lexer decodes the source into `Vec<char>`
// once so `chars[i]` is O(1) codepoint access. The `.myc` surface has no such buffer; the source is
// kept as raw `Bytes` (UTF-8) and scanned BYTE-wise. This is behaviorally identical for this
// grammar: every structural character (punctuation, digits, keyword letters, escape markers) is
// ASCII, and ASCII bytes never collide with a UTF-8 continuation byte (continuation bytes are
// always >= 0x80). So a `"` / `\` / newline / keyword letter is unambiguously recognized scanning
// bytes, exactly as scanning chars would. Only [`step_pos`] needs to know the difference: it bumps
// the COLUMN only on non-continuation bytes (mirroring "count codepoints, not bytes" — the
// `is_cont_byte` predicate is the same 0x80..0xBF test `lib/std/text.myc::is_cont_byte` already
// established for UTF-8 decoding).
//
// FLAG-lex-2 (literal-payload tokens carry Bytes verbatim; no eager numeric conversion at all,
// INCLUDING `Int`). token.myc's FLAG-token-1/2 already carry `Ident`/`BinLit`/`BytesLit`/`TritLit`/
// `StrLit`/`FloatLit`/`Int` as `Bytes`. This lexer does not even attempt the decimal/exponent FLOAT
// EXTENSION Rust's `lex_int` performs (the `.` + fractional-digit / `e|E` + exponent lookahead) —
// every digit run here lexes as `Int` only; a `.` after digits is left as a separate [`Tok::Dot`]
// token (never consumed into a float). This is a real, deliberate scope narrowing (not just a
// deferred conversion): no accept-corpus file (`docs/spec/grammar/conformance/accept/`) contains a
// float literal (verified by grep during authoring), so nothing in the Stage-1 gate exercises this
// gap, but it IS a true behavioral difference from the oracle and is reported as such, not silently
// narrowed. A follow-up stage should port `lex_int`'s float-extension lookahead + the finite-value
// gate (FLAG-lex-3) faithfully.
//
// FLAG-lex-3 (no float finite-value / overflow gate). Because floats are not scanned as a distinct
// literal form (FLAG-lex-2), the finite-value / out-of-range refusal `lexer.rs::lex_int` performs
// for `FloatLit` (ADR-040 §2.4: a literal whose correctly-rounded binary64 magnitude is not finite
// is an explicit error) has no analog here. Also not enforced: `Int`'s own i64-range refusal
// (`s.parse::<i64>()` failing) — moot here since `Int` carries verbatim digits, not a converted
// value (FLAG-lex-2/token.myc FLAG-token-2). Neither gap is exercised by the accept-corpus.
//
// FLAG-lex-4 (ASCII-only whitespace, not `char::is_whitespace`). `skip_trivia` treats exactly
// space/tab/CR/LF as trivia; Rust's `c.is_whitespace()` recognizes the broader Unicode White_Space
// set. No accept-corpus file uses non-ASCII whitespace (grep-verified), so this is behaviorally
// identical over the Stage-1 gate's actual input, but is a real, narrower gap than the oracle.
//
// FLAG-lex-5 (comment capture — `lex_with_comments`/`Comment` — is OUT OF SCOPE for this stage).
// The token-STREAM differential (DN-26 §7.3) is defined over the token stream `lex` produces, which
// already discards comments identically to Rust's plain `lex` path; the `mycfmt`-only comment
// side-channel (`Comment`, `lex_with_comments`) belongs to a much later self-hosting stage (the
// self-hosted formatter) and is not ported here.
//
// FLAG-lex-6 (checker bug — nested-constructor match panics; see
// `crates/mycelium-l1/tests/compiler_stage1.rs`'s `FLAG-stage1-checker-1` for the full isolation).
// A combined two-level pattern `Some(Scalar(SF16))` (unwrapping `Option[Tok]` and a payload
// constructor in ONE match arm) panics `usefulness::useful_budgeted` when the outer type has ~80
// variants (`Tok`). This nodule's OWN logic never matches on `Tok` at all (it only CONSTRUCTS
// `Tok` values — `keyword`'s internal matching is on `Bytes`, inherited unchanged from
// `compiler.token`), so the bug does not affect `lex` itself; it only constrains how the
// DIFFERENTIAL TEST inspects the resulting token stream (documented at the test call site).

// ── Option (local; no cross-leaf import) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
type Option[A] = Some(A) | None;

// ── Result (local; no cross-leaf import) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
type Result[A, E] = Ok(A) | Err(E);

// ── Pair (local helper product) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
type Pair[A, B] = Pr(A, B);

// ── Pos (redeclared from compiler.token — FLAG-lex-0) ───────────────────────────────────────────
type Pos = P(Binary{32}, Binary{32});

fn pos_line(p: Pos) => Binary{32} =
  match p { P(l, _) => l };

fn pos_col(p: Pos) => Binary{32} =
  match p { P(_, c) => c };

// ── ScalarTok / StrengthTok (redeclared from compiler.token — FLAG-lex-0/token.myc FLAG-token-3) ──
type ScalarTok = SF16 | SBf16 | SF32 | SF64;
type StrengthTok = GExact | GProven | GEmpirical | GDeclared;

// ── Tok (redeclared verbatim from compiler.token — FLAG-lex-0) ─────────────────────────────────
type Tok =
    Nodule | Phylum | Colony
  | Hypha | Fuse | Mesh | Graft | Cyst | Xloc | Forage | Backbone | Tier | Reclaim
  | Consume | Grow | Derive
  | Use | Pub | Priv | Type | Trait | Impl | Fn | Matured | Thaw
  | Let | In | If | Then | Else | Match | For | Swap
  | Default | Paradigm | With | Wild | Spore | To | Policy
  | Lambda | Object | Via | Lower
  | KwBinary | KwTernary | KwDense | Vsa
  | BinShort | TernShort | EmbShort | HvecShort
  | KwSeq | KwBytes | KwFloat | KwSubstrate | KwSparse
  | Scalar(ScalarTok) | Strength(StrengthTok)
  | Ident(Bytes)
  | BinLit(Bytes)
  | BytesLit(Bytes)
  | TritLit(Bytes)
  | StrLit(Bytes)
  | Int(Bytes)
  | FloatLit(Bytes)
  | LParen | RParen | LBrace | RBrace | LBracket | RBracket
  | LAngle | RAngle | Shl | Shr
  | At | AtStdSys
  | Colon | Comma | Semi | Dot | Pipe
  | Plus | Minus | Star | Slash | Percent | Caret | Amp | AmpAmp
  | Eq | EqEq | Arrow | FatArrow | Bang | BangEq | PipePipe
  | Eof;

// ── Spanned (redeclared from compiler.token — FLAG-lex-0) ──────────────────────────────────────
type Spanned = Sp(Tok, Pos);

fn sp_tok(s: Spanned) => Tok =
  match s { Sp(t, _) => t };

fn sp_pos(s: Spanned) => Pos =
  match s { Sp(_, p) => p };

// ── keyword (redeclared verbatim from compiler.token — FLAG-lex-0) ─────────────────────────────
// Identical to compiler.token::keyword; see token.myc for the full rationale/provenance note. Kept
// byte-for-byte identical here so a future cross-nodule-execution enabler can delete this copy and
// `use compiler.token.keyword` with no behavior change.
fn keyword(word: Bytes) => Option[Tok] =
    match bytes_eq(word, "nodule") {
      0b1 => Some(Nodule),
      _ =>
      match bytes_eq(word, "phylum") {
        0b1 => Some(Phylum),
        _ =>
        match bytes_eq(word, "colony") {
          0b1 => Some(Colony),
          _ =>
          match bytes_eq(word, "hypha") {
            0b1 => Some(Hypha),
            _ =>
            match bytes_eq(word, "fuse") {
              0b1 => Some(Fuse),
              _ =>
              match bytes_eq(word, "mesh") {
                0b1 => Some(Mesh),
                _ =>
                match bytes_eq(word, "graft") {
                  0b1 => Some(Graft),
                  _ =>
                  match bytes_eq(word, "cyst") {
                    0b1 => Some(Cyst),
                    _ =>
                    match bytes_eq(word, "xloc") {
                      0b1 => Some(Xloc),
                      _ =>
                      match bytes_eq(word, "forage") {
                        0b1 => Some(Forage),
                        _ =>
                        match bytes_eq(word, "backbone") {
                          0b1 => Some(Backbone),
                          _ =>
                          match bytes_eq(word, "tier") {
                            0b1 => Some(Tier),
                            _ =>
                            match bytes_eq(word, "reclaim") {
                              0b1 => Some(Reclaim),
                              _ =>
                              match bytes_eq(word, "consume") {
                                0b1 => Some(Consume),
                                _ =>
                                match bytes_eq(word, "grow") {
                                  0b1 => Some(Grow),
                                  _ =>
                                  match bytes_eq(word, "lambda") {
                                    0b1 => Some(Lambda),
                                    _ =>
                                    match bytes_eq(word, "object") {
                                      0b1 => Some(Object),
                                      _ =>
                                      match bytes_eq(word, "via") {
                                        0b1 => Some(Via),
                                        _ =>
                                        match bytes_eq(word, "lower") {
                                          0b1 => Some(Lower),
                                          _ =>
                                          match bytes_eq(word, "derive") {
                                            0b1 => Some(Derive),
                                            _ =>
                                            match bytes_eq(word, "use") {
                                              0b1 => Some(Use),
                                              _ =>
                                              match bytes_eq(word, "pub") {
                                                0b1 => Some(Pub),
                                                _ =>
                                                match bytes_eq(word, "priv") {
                                                0b1 => Some(Priv),
                                                _ =>
                                                match bytes_eq(word, "type") {
                                                  0b1 => Some(Type),
                                                  _ =>
                                                  match bytes_eq(word, "trait") {
                                                    0b1 => Some(Trait),
                                                    _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "impl") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Impl),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "fn") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Fn),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "matured") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Matured),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "thaw") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Thaw),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "let") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Let),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "in") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(In),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "if") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(If),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "then") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Then),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "else") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Else),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "match") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Match),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "for") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(For),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "swap") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Swap),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "default") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Default),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "paradigm") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Paradigm),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "with") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(With),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "wild") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Wild),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "spore") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Spore),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "to") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(To),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "policy") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Policy),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Binary") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(KwBinary),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Ternary") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(KwTernary),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Dense") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(KwDense),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "VSA") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Vsa),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "bin") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(BinShort),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "tern") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(TernShort),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "emb") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(EmbShort),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "hvec") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(HvecShort),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Seq") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(KwSeq),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Bytes") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(KwBytes),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Float") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(KwFloat),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Substrate") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(KwSubstrate),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Sparse") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(KwSparse),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "F16") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Scalar(SF16)),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "BF16") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Scalar(SBf16)),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "F32") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Scalar(SF32)),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "F64") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Scalar(SF64)),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Exact") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Strength(GExact)),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Proven") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Strength(GProven)),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Empirical") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Strength(GEmpirical)),
                                                      _ =>
                                                    match bytes_eq(word, "Declared") {
                                                      0b1 => Some(Strength(GDeclared)),
                                                      _ =>
                                                      None
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
                                                    }
